<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-05-29T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-05-29T21:00:00-05:00" n="768" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d768">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51 Relief Credits/118: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Washburn</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-29T22:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 29,
                                        1928—10 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>27. Regret to inform you Congress adjourned today without acting upon
                            Bill authorizing subordination of lien and debt settlement.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>